.TH "get_bm_events_by_type" 9 "get_bm_events_by_type" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_bm_events_by_type \- returns bitmap of supported events per @type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const unsigned long *" get_bm_events_by_type
.BI "(struct input_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "int type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
input device from which bitmap is retrieved
.IP "type" 12
type of button (EV_KEY, EV_SW)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return value of this function can be used to allocate bitmap
large enough to hold all bits for given type.
